
[1]threat

   THREAT, n. thret. A menace; denunciation of ill; declaration of an
   intention or determination to inflict punishment, loss or pain on
   another.

   There is no terror, Cassius, in your threats.

     THREAT, v.t. thret. To threaten, which see. Threat is used only in
                                   poetry.
